		<title lang="en"><![CDATA[Anti-Snooping]]></title>
		<description lang="en"><![CDATA[When someone visits the URL of a forum they aren't authorised to access it says 'You are not authorised to read this forum', which can cause them to try find out what the forum is. Instead this mod makes it display 'The forum you selected does not exist'.]]></description>
		<author-group>
			<author>
				<realname><![CDATA[Michael Cullum]]></realname>
				<username><![CDATA[Unknown Bliss]]></username>
				<homepage><![CDATA[http://unknownbliss.co.uk]]></homepage>
				<email><![CDATA[unknownbliss@phpbb.ce.ms]]></email>
			</author>
		</author-group>
		<mod-version>2.0.0</mod-version>
		<installation>
			<level>easy</level>
			<time>60</time>
			<target-version>3.0.7-PL1</target-version>
		</installation>
		<history>
			<entry>
				<date>2010-09-19</date>
				<rev-version>1.0.0</rev-version>
				<changelog lang="en">
					<change><![CDATA[MOD Created with forum message]]></change>
				</changelog>
			</entry>
			<entry>
				<date>2010-09-20</date>
				<rev-version>2.0.0</rev-version>
				<changelog lang="en">
					<change><![CDATA[Added Extra messages than just forum message]]></change>
				</changelog>
			</entry>
		</history>
	</header>
	<action-group>
		<open src="language/en/common.php">
			<edit>
				<find><![CDATA[	'SORRY_AUTH_READ'			=> 'You are not authorised to read this forum.',]]></find>
				<action type="replace-with"><![CDATA[	'SORRY_AUTH_READ'			=> 'The forum you selected does not exist.',]]></action>
			</edit>
		</open>
	</action-group>
</mod>
